A principal finding that we analyze in detail below is that price efficiency in the market for the stock is higher when the intrinsic value of the option is positive (in the money). This effect is very strong, is present in all four cohorts, and is highly significant when we use a matched‐pairst‐test to compare a single mean level of price efficiency for each cohort when the ex post value of the option is in the money, with a single mean when the option is out of the money (
