sec.p:
Overall liquidity trader profits are decreasing in the magnitude of the liquidity shocks but increasing in the correlation between the net liquidity shock and the insider’s information: when the liquidity traders are required to trade in the direction of the insider’s information, their profits are higher. Both of these effects are highly significant (
